## ✅ Step-by-Step Roadmap (No money, only skill)

### 1️⃣ Define Requirements (Functional + Non-functional)

Don’t code without this. That’s how poor devs stay poor.

### 2️⃣ System Design (High-level architecture)

Draw before coding. CPU is cheaper than regret.

### 3️⃣ Design Database Schema (PostgreSQL)

Entities:

* user
* tweet
* follow
* like
* retweet
* media
* notifications

### 4️⃣ Write API Contracts (before writing backend)

Example:

```
POST /api/tweet
body: { text, media? }
response: { id, created_at }
```

### 5️⃣ Set Up Dev Environment

* GitHub repo
* Prettier + ESLint
* .env file
* Docker file
* Dev DB local

### 6️⃣ Build Core MVP Features

✅ Signup / Login
✅ Post tweet
✅ Follow / Unfollow
✅ Feed (fan-out or fan-in)
✅ Like / Retweet

No DM, no search, no notifications, no video uploads until MVP works.

### 7️⃣ Add Caching (after proving DB bottleneck)

* Redis or KeyDB (self host on 1$ VPS or use free containers)

### 8️⃣ Add Background Jobs (BullMQ with Redis)

For:

* feed generation
* notifications
* email

### 9️⃣ Add Search (Meilisearch) ONLY if needed

### 🔟 Deploy Full Stack (all free services)

| Service  | Host                      |
| -------- | ------------------------- |
| Frontend | Vercel free               |
| Backend  | Railway / Render          |
| DB       | Neon / Supabase / Railway |
| Redis    | Fly.io self host          |
| Search   | Railway free container    |
| Storage  | Cloudflare R2             |

